{
  "texts": [
    "It is possible that other themes would emerge using different coding procedures, such as different thematic categories or more precise definitions of these categories, increasing inter-rater reliability.",
    "Future research should explore these possibilities but with recognition of the post hoc nature of participants' interpretations of their source judgments.",
    "One reason why the LLM did not pass our source attribution test could be that the moral evaluation task was too simplistic.",
    "Whether people can distinguish between human and LLM moral discourse depends on precisely how that task is defined.",
    "Efforts to increase task difficulty, for instance, could administer evaluative passages derived from a human sample that is specifically trained in ethics (e.g., graduate students or faculty in philosophy)."
  ]
}